Ontology Specification Draft

Abstract

This ontology's purpose is to link events, restaurants, transport services, hotels and attractions, with cities acting as central nodes. Taking the average ratings from user reviews and the usual prices for each different resource (where applicable), the established semantic properties will allow users to find out what each city or each type of resource have to offer.

Introduction back to ToC

The resources that make up OntoTravel are a defined set of cities along with their associated resources, comprised of hotels, events, restaurants, transport services and attractions. Additionally, the most relevant concept of the ontology is its capacity to be easily expanded through the common object properties hasCity, hasPrice and hasRating.

OntoTravel: a travel ontology: Description back to ToC

This ontology's purpose is to link events, restaurants, transport services, hotels and attractions, with cities acting as a central node

Cross-reference for OntoTravel: a travel ontology classes, object properties and data properties back to ToC

This section provides details for each class and property defined by OntoTravel: a travel ontology.

AveragePricedHotel Ruleback to ToC or SWRL ToC

If an hotel room rate is equal or over 100 and equal or under 200, it is considered it has an average price

hasPrice op(?hotel,?price) , lessThanOrEqual(?) , greaterThanOrEqual(?) , hasPriceValue dp(?price,?value) , Hotel c(?hotel) -> AveragePricedHotel c(?hotel)

AveragePricedRestaurant Ruleback to ToC or SWRL ToC

If a restaurant cost is equal or over 25 and equal or under 50, it is considered it has an average price

Restaurant c(?restaurant) , greaterThanOrEqual(?) , hasPriceValue dp(?price,?value) , hasPrice op(?restaurant,?price) , lessThanOrEqual(?) -> AveragePricedRestaurant c(?restaurant)

AveragePricedTransport Ruleback to ToC or SWRL ToC

If a specific transport's average cost is equal or over 4 and equal or under 7, it is considered it has an average price

Transport c(?transport) , lessThanOrEqual(?) , greaterThanOrEqual(?) , hasPriceValue dp(?price,?value) , hasPrice op(?transport,?price) -> AveragePricedTransport c(?transport)

AverageRatedAttraction Ruleback to ToC or SWRL ToC

If an attraction has a rating equal or over 3.5 and under 4, it is considered average

hasRating op(?attraction,?rating) , hasRatingValue dp(?rating,?value) , greaterThanOrEqual(?) , lessThan(?) , Attraction c(?attraction) -> AverageRatedAttraction c(?attraction)

AverageRatedHotel Ruleback to ToC or SWRL ToC

If an hotel has a rating equal or over 3.5 and under 4, it is considered average

hasRating op(?hotel,?rating) , hasRatingValue dp(?rating,?value) , greaterThanOrEqual(?) , lessThan(?) , Hotel c(?hotel) -> AverageRatedHotel c(?hotel)

AverageRatedRestaurant Ruleback to ToC or SWRL ToC

If a restaurant has a rating equal or over 3.5 and under 4, it is considered average

hasRatingValue dp(?rating,?value) , greaterThanOrEqual(?) , Restaurant c(?restaurant) , hasRating op(?restaurant,?rating) , lessThan(?) -> AverageRatedRestaurant c(?restaurant)

BadlyRatedAttraction Ruleback to ToC or SWRL ToC

If an attraction has a rating under 3.5, it is considered bad

hasRating op(?attraction,?rating) , lessThan(?) , hasRatingValue dp(?rating,?value) , Attraction c(?attraction) -> BadRatedAttraction c(?attraction)

BadlyRatedHotel Ruleback to ToC or SWRL ToC

If an hotel has a rating under 3.5, it is considered bad

lessThan(?) , hasRating op(?hotel,?rating) , hasRatingValue dp(?rating,?value) , Hotel c(?hotel) -> BadRatedHotel c(?hotel)

BadlyRatedRestaurant Ruleback to ToC or SWRL ToC

If a restaurant has a rating under 3.5, it is considered bad

lessThan(?) , hasRatingValue dp(?rating,?value) , Restaurant c(?restaurant) , hasRating op(?restaurant,?rating) -> BadlyRatedRestaurant c(?restaurant)

BudgetCityback to ToC or SWRL ToC

Cities with both cheap restaurants and hotels

CheapRestaurant c(?restaurant) , CheapHotel c(?hotel) , isCityOf op(?city,?restaurant) , isCityOf op(?city,?hotel) , City c(?city) -> BudgetCity c(?city)

CheapHotel Ruleback to ToC or SWRL ToC

If an hotel room rate is under 100, it is considered cheap

hasPrice op(?hotel,?price) , lessThan(?) , hasPriceValue dp(?price,?value) , Hotel c(?hotel) -> CheapHotel c(?hotel)

CheapRestaurant Ruleback to ToC or SWRL ToC

If a restaurant cost per person is under 20, it is considered cheap

Restaurant c(?restaurant) , lessThan(?) , hasPriceValue dp(?price,?value) , hasPrice op(?restaurant,?price) -> CheapRestaurant c(?restaurant)

CheapTransport Ruleback to ToC or SWRL ToC

If a specific transport's cost is under 4, it is considered cheap

Transport c(?transport) , lessThan(?) , hasPriceValue dp(?price,?value) , hasPrice op(?transport,?price) -> CheapTransport c(?transport)

ConcertCityback to ToC or SWRL ToC

Cities where music events have been scheduled

hasEventType op(?event,?Music_event) , isCityOf op(?city,?event) , City c(?city) -> ConcertCity c(?city)

ExpensiveHotel Ruleback to ToC or SWRL ToC

If an hotel room rate is over 200, it is considered expensive

hasPrice op(?hotel,?price) , hasPriceValue dp(?price,?value) , greaterThan(?) , Hotel c(?hotel) -> ExpensiveHotel c(?hotel)

ExpensiveRestaurant Ruleback to ToC or SWRL ToC

If a restaurant cost per person is over 50, it is considered expensive

Restaurant c(?restaurant) , greaterThan(?) , hasPriceValue dp(?price,?value) , hasPrice op(?restaurant,?price) -> ExpensiveRestaurant c(?restaurant)

ExpensiveTransport Ruleback to ToC or SWRL ToC

If a specific transport's cost is over 7, it is considered expensive

Transport c(?transport) , hasPriceValue dp(?price,?value) , hasPrice op(?transport,?price) , greaterThan(?) -> ExpensiveTransport c(?transport)

GoodRatedAttraction Ruleback to ToC or SWRL ToC

If an attraction has a rating equal or over 4 and under 4.5, it is considered good

hasRating op(?attraction,?rating) , hasRatingValue dp(?rating,?value) , lessThan(?) , Attraction c(?attraction) , greaterThanOrEqual(?) -> GoodRatedAttraction c(?attraction)

GoodRatedHotel Ruleback to ToC or SWRL ToC

If an hotel has a rating equal or over 4 and under 4.5, it is considered good

hasRating op(?hotel,?rating) , hasRatingValue dp(?rating,?value) , lessThan(?) , Hotel c(?hotel) , greaterThanOrEqual(?) -> GoodRatedHotel c(?hotel)

GoodRatedRestaurant Ruleback to ToC or SWRL ToC

If a restaurant has a rating equal or over 4.0 and under 4.5, it is considered average

hasRatingValue dp(?rating,?value) , lessThan(?) , Restaurant c(?restaurant) , hasRating op(?restaurant,?rating) , greaterThanOrEqual(?) -> GoodRatedRestaurant c(?restaurant)

TechHubCityback to ToC or SWRL ToC

Cities with business-oriented hotels where technological events take place

hasHotelType op(?hotel,?hoteltype) , hasEventType op(?event,?eventtype) , , isCityOf op(?city,?event) , isCityOf op(?city,?hotel) , City c(?city) , -> TechHub c(?city)

VeryGoodRatedAttraction Ruleback to ToC or SWRL ToC

If an attraction has a rating equal or over 4.5, it is considered very good

hasRating op(?attraction,?rating) , hasRatingValue dp(?rating,?value) , greaterThanOrEqual(?) , Attraction c(?attraction) -> VeryGoodRatedAttraction c(?attraction)

VeryGoodRatedHotel Ruleback to ToC or SWRL ToC

If an hotel has a rating equal or over 4.5, it is considered very good

hasRating op(?hotel,?rating) , hasRatingValue dp(?rating,?value) , greaterThanOrEqual(?) , Hotel c(?hotel) -> VeryGoodRatedHotel c(?hotel)

VeryGoodRatedRestaurant Ruleback to ToC or SWRL ToC

If a restaurant has a rating equal or over 4.5, it is considered very good

hasRatingValue dp(?rating,?value) , greaterThanOrEqual(?) , Restaurant c(?restaurant) , hasRating op(?restaurant,?rating) -> VeryGoodRatedRestaurant c(?restaurant)
